            <title>[DERBY-624] Running derbynetclientmats and derbynetmats requires accessDeclaredMembers permission to be granted with sane=true</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-624</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;About 17 tests fail if this permission is not granted. Permission should not be required to run Derby in embedded or network server mode.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;permission java.lang.RuntimePermission &quot;accessDeclaredMembers&quot;;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In some (all?) cases it is because getDeclaredConstrunctor or getDeclaredMethod is called when the getPublic versions would suffice.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
